{"word":"ἀγέρωχος","slug":"ἀγέρωχος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγέρωχος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:derived, derivation'>Deriv.</a> uncertain.\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <i>high-minded, lordly</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; in <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b> of <i>noble</i> actions.<p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in bad sense, <i>haughty, arrogant, insolent</i>, <b><a href='S:Archilochus Lyricus'>Archil.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b>: so <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-χως</el>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b> <p/></div>"}]}